OL,3,CUndercover police inquiry to hear
OL,4,Cjustice campaigners' 'deeply moving'
OL,5,Cevidence
OL,7,FIt also apologised again to women who
OL,8,Fwere deceived into relationships with
OL,9,Fofficers, and bereaved families whose
OL,10,Fchildren's details were used as cover
OL,11,Fidentities without their permission.
OL,13,FMr Skelton said: "There was a
OL,14,Fcollective failure to exercise ethical
OL,15,Fjudgment about the purpose of
OL,16,Fundercover policing and the propriety
OL,17,Fof reporting on family justice
OL,18,Fcampaigns.
OL,26,@uD@ROU
